Package: ZIDW
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2025-09-15
Title: Tools for Analyzing Zero-Inflated Discrete Weibull Models
Authors@R: c(person("Peng", "Yeh", role = c("aut"),
	email = "peng.yeh@merck.com"),
	person("Derek S.", "Young", role = c("aut", "cre"),
	email = "derek.young@uky.edu", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3048-3803")))
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports: DWreg, actuar, maxLik, COUNT, gtools, matrixcalc, DiscreteWeibull, dplyr, ggplot2, purrr, tibble
URL: https://github.com/dsy109/ZIDW
Description: Functions for analyzing zero-inflated discrete Weibull (ZIDW) regression models. 
    This package includes the parameter estimations for both regression and univariate settings, 
    the distribution functions, functions to generate randomized quantile residuals and a pseudo R2,
    and plotting of rootograms.
